  "text": "R 0 is the number of secondary infections generated by a primary infection in a completely susceptible population during the entire duration of infectiousness and, as such, is a measure of transmission potential. For vector-borne diseases, multiple R 0 can be estimated (e.g., human-to-mosquito, mosquito-tohuman, human-to-human). Here, we estimate the number of secondary human infections that arise from 1 infectious human as mediated through the vector, as proposed by Ferguson et al in 1999 [CITATION_1] . As with λ(t), we provide average estimates of R 0 across all serotypes, as well as serotype-specific estimates. Our estimates of R 0 assume that individuals can be infected by up to 2 serotypes and are afterward immune to further infection.",
